  },
  {
    q: "Should we focus on LinkedIn Ads or Google Ads for a B2B SaaS product?",
    a: "Both serve different moments in the buyer journey. Google Ads captures buyers who are actively searching for a solution right now. LinkedIn reaches your ideal customer profile before they are searching, building awareness and familiarity. For most B2B SaaS products we recommend running both with different budgets and messaging based on your product's sales cycle length."
  },
  {
    q: "How do we measure ROI from digital marketing for a SaaS product?",
    a: "We track demo requests attributed to each channel, lead-to-demo conversion rate, and when possible the downstream close rate and ARR from inbound leads. We set up Google Analytics 4 with proper conversion events so you can see exactly which campaigns, content pieces, and landing pages are generating the most valuable pipeline."
  },
  {
    q: "Can you help an IT services company in Ahmedabad attract clients from other Indian cities?",
    a: "Absolutely. Many of our tech clients are Ahmedabad-based companies serving clients in Mumbai, Delhi, Bangalore, and Hyderabad. A strong website with excellent case studies, clear service pages, and Google Ads targeting buyers in those cities can generate strong inbound from across India regardless of your physical location."
  },
  {
    q: "What kind of email sequences work best for SaaS demo nurturing?",
    a: "After a demo request, sequences should include a confirmation and prep email, a pre-demo case study relevant to the prospect's industry, and post-demo follow-up emails at day 3, day 7, and day 14 if they have not moved forward. Each email should provide value rather than just checking in. We design these sequences based on your product category and typical sales cycle."
  }
];
